## 6) Database Model and Migration Details

## 6.1 SQLAlchemy models present
- tasks
- task_history
- habits
- expenses
- finance_assets
- finance_liabilities
- finance_transactions
- finance_recurring_rules
- finance_recurring_occurrences
- finance_monthly_budgets
- finance_category_budgets
- finance_goals
- finance_goal_allocations
- finance_audit_log

### 6.2 Key field-level notes
- tasks:
  - recurrence and recurrence_completed_on support recurring completion semantics.
  - labels stored as JSON string in Text column.
- finance amounts generally Numeric(14,2).
- finance_transactions includes payment_mode nullable string.
- audit/history tables store before/after or changes JSON strings.

### 6.3 Relationship and integrity reality
Important implementation split:
- SQLAlchemy models mostly use plain Integer ids and do not declare ForeignKey constraints.
- Migration scripts create_finance_networth_tables.py add real FK constraints and indexes.

Consequence:
- If DB is built via Base.metadata.create_all only, constraints/indexes/uniques from migration SQL may be missing.
- If migration scripts were run against DB, constraints may exist.
- This can produce environment drift and inconsistent behavior/performance.

### 6.4 Migration/state observations
- payment_mode support exists in model + startup additive migration + dedicated migration script.
- old tasks migration/scripts still reference estimated_minutes, but current Task model removed it.
- stale scripts/tests referencing estimated_minutes are now inconsistent with live schema.

