## 9) Notable Implementation Gaps and Inconsistencies

1. Legacy expenses API is unreachable.
- expenses router not mounted.

2. Frontend listFinanceGoals(includeInactive) parameter is ignored.
- API client always calls /api/expense/goals without active_only query.
- Dashboard expecting active-only may include inactive goals.

3. Bills/EMI UX mismatch.
- Bills page submit path forces txn_type='expense', so true liability_payment recurring rules are not produced there.
- Dashboard Add Bill allows selecting liability_payment, but UI does not collect liability_id, which backend requires when posting occurrence.
- Result: liability_payment recurring flow is effectively incomplete.

4. Goal allocations are backend-supported but no first-class frontend management flow is present.

5. Dashboard home placeholders.
- Main root dashboard still says habits/analytics are not implemented even though separate pages exist; this is a product cohesion gap.

6. Migration strategy drift.
- create_all startup path and SQL migration scripts define schema with different richness (constraints/indexes).

