## 12) Recommended Next Build Sequence (from current code state)

1. Security baseline
- auth + user model + user scoping
- pagination + rate limiting
- CORS tightening

2. Data integrity and migration cleanup
- choose one migration source of truth (Alembic recommended)
- align create_all vs migration schema definitions
- remove/repair stale estimated_minutes scripts/tests

3. Finance flow completion
- complete liability_payment recurring UX (collect liability_id in bill forms)
- wire goal allocation UX
- add stricter finance validation

4. Product cohesion
- update root dashboard cards to reflect real module maturity
- unify habits/analytics summaries into dashboard

5. Testing maturity
- add pytest backend API tests and deterministic DB fixtures
- add frontend integration tests for critical flows (task CRUD, transaction CRUD, recurring posting)

---

## 13) Bottom Line
The project already contains substantial and useful functionality, especially in tasks and finance.
The largest risk is security and multi-user readiness, not feature scarcity.
If this remains a local single-user app, it is already practical.
If this moves to shared or internet-accessible use, security and tenant isolation must be implemented first.
